events.name: Alabama Crimson Tide at Georgia Bulldogs

headlines.description: AJ McCarron threw a 45-yard touchdown pass to Amari Cooper with 3:15 remaining, and No. 2 Alabama advanced to a national championship showdown with Notre Dame by holding off No. 3 Georgia 32-28 in a thrilling Southeastern Conference title game Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bama wins SEC, heads to BCS

events.name: Texas Longhorns at Kansas State Wildcats

headlines.description: Collin Klein threw a touchdown pass and ran for two scores and  Kansas State beat Texas 42-24 on Saturday night for its third conference title in 117 years and a trip to the Fiesta Bowl.

events.name: Oklahoma Sooners at TCU Horned Frogs

headlines.description: Landry Jones threw for 244 yards and two touchdowns, Damien Williams ran untouched 66 yards for a score and 12th-ranked Oklahoma held on to win 24-17 at TCU on Saturday and clinch at least a share of the Big 12 title.

events.name: Nebraska Cornhuskers at Wisconsin Badgers

headlines.description: Montee Ball ran for 201 yards and three touchdowns, and Wisconsin rushed for the 539 yards to rout Nebraska 70-31 in the Big Ten title game on Saturday night.

events.name: Florida State Seminoles at Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets

headlines.description: James Wilder Jr. ran two touchdowns as No. 13 Florida State held off Georgia Tech 21-15 Saturday night to capture its first Atlantic Coast Conference championship since 2005 and earn a trip to the Orange Bowl.
headlines.shortLinkText: FSU holds on for Orange Bowl berth

events.name: Nicholls State Colonels at Oregon State Beavers

headlines.description: Storm Woods ran for two touchdowns in the first quarter and Oregon State (No. 15 BCS, No. 16 AP) put up its highest point total ever, routing Nicholls State 77-3 on Saturday in a game postponed by Hurricane Isaac.
headlines.shortLinkText: Oregon State sets record for points in romp

events.name: Boise State Broncos at Nevada Wolf Pack

headlines.description: Joe Southwick threw two touchdown passes to lead Boise State (No. 20 BCS, No. 25 AP) to a 27-21 victory over Nevada, earning the Broncos a share of the Mountain West Conference title and ensuring their nation's best seventh consecutive 10-win season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Boise St. tops Nevada, earns share of MWC

events.name: Oklahoma State Cowboys at Baylor Bears

headlines.description: Lache Seastrunk rushed for 178 yards, including a 76-yard touchdown in the fourth quarter, and Nick Florence passed for 296 yards as Baylor beat Oklahoma State (No. 23 BCS, No. 24 AP) 41-34 Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Seastrunk gashes Oklahoma State, lifts Baylor

events.name: UCF Knights at Tulsa Golden Hurricane

headlines.description: Alex Singleton ran for 100 yards and plunged over the top for a 1-yard score in overtime to lift Tulsa to a 33-27 victory over UCF on Saturday in the Conference USA championship game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tulsa secures first C-USA crown since 2005

events.name: Kansas Jayhawks at West Virginia Mountaineers

headlines.description: Geno Smith threw for 407 yards and three touchdowns in his final home game to lead West Virginia to a 59-10 win over Kansas on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Smith throws for 40 TDs in season as WVU rolls

events.name: Middle Tennessee Blue Raiders at Arkansas State Red Wolves

headlines.description: Ryan Aplin broke his own Arkansas State record for passing touchdowns in a season and the Red Wolves captured their second straight Sun Belt Conference championship with a 45-0 victory over Middle Tennessee on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Arkansas State wins 2nd straight Sun Belt title

events.name: Louisiana Ragin' Cajuns at Florida Atlantic Owls
Cincinnati Bearcats at Connecticut Huskies

headlines.description: Brendon Kay threw two touchdown passes to Travis Kelce, and caught one from the big tight end on a trick play as Cincinnati beat Connecticut 34-17 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cincy tops UConn for share of Big East title

events.name: New Mexico State Aggies at Texas State Bobcats
Pittsburgh Panthers at South Florida Bulls

headlines.description: Ray Graham rushed for a pair of touchdowns and went over 1,000 yards Saturday night to help Pittsburgh become bowl eligible with a 27-3 rout of struggling South Florida.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pitt rolls South Florida to become bowl eligible
